The issue here is, that the PHP embedding is replaced with the token `__UNKNOWN__` and the JS parser basicly sees:

```javascript
    var formBox = new FormBox;
    formBox.display({
    form : document.getElementById('thisForm')
            , buttons : [
            {icon : 'search.png', label : 'View', name : 'View', submitAction : true}
__UNKNOWN__
                , {icon : 'delete.png', label : 'Delete', name : 'Delete', submitAction : true}
__UNKNOWN__
            ]
            , deleteConfirm : 1
    });
```

This is indeed invalid code. Not sure yet how to handle this.

